news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces' profit rises 24% to ₹19 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income increased to Rs 174.14 crore during January-March period of 2024-25 from Rs 120.10 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing on Tuesday.

news.title: Telangana government to launch land survey in 413 villages lacking maps, records
news.para: Remarkably, several villages, such as Laxmapur in Mudu Chintalapally of Medchal Malkajgiri district, have no formal land records or village maps.

news.title: Gurugram civic body serves notices to 22 property tax defaulters who owe over ₹50 lakh
news.para: Due to ongoing issues with property ID corrections, the municipal body issued an advisory on Tuesday, instructing residents to report directly to the Commissioner or Additional Commissioner if anyone solicits money for property tax-related services or corrections.

news.title: Ghaziabad master plan cleared, RRTS & metro corridors set for transit-oriented development
news.para: The master plan, which covers an overall developed area of 33,543.1 hectares—18,687.8 hectares in Ghaziabad, 6,874.9 hectares in Modinagar and 7,980.4 hectares in Loni— will come into effect once the state govt issues a gazette notification, which is expected within a month, an official from GDA said.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB considers new demand survey after prices of flats increase sharply
news.para: In the demand survey for the scheme held in February-March this year, nearly 7,500 applicants expressed interest in 372 flats. In a previous survey (2018-19), the scheme received only 178 applications.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates apartment complex in Karur
news.para: Each of the 32 apartments measures 400sqft and includes a bedroom, living room, kitchen, bathroom, and toilet, with an individual unit estimated to cost 9.23 lakh. As part of the initiative, 30 beneficiaries were issued allotment orders during the inauguration ceremony.

news.title: Delhi civic body's house tax amnesty scheme to waive arrears & boost revenue
news.para: Under the scheme, taxpayers only need to settle outstanding dues for the previous five years along with current bills for dues up to 2004 to be waived.

news.title: MMRDA secures ₹1,500-crore loan for redevelopment project in Mumbai’s Ghatkopar
news.para: To ensure financial viability, MMRDA has devised a multi-source funding strategy. Out of the total Rs 8,498 crore project cost, Rs 3,916 crore will be raised through loans.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body simplifies house tax payment with QR code stickers
news.para: A QR code sticker will be generated for each bill and pasted on houses, similar to electricity meters. This digital initiative aims to speed up tax recovery.

news.title: Rajasthan HC asks for compliance report in illegal Walled City buildings case
news.para: The bench of Justice Indrajit Singh and Justice Anand Sharma gave this order while hearing the application filed by the building owners.

news.title: DDA to launch new housing scheme with units in Narela, Loknayakpuram
news.para: The latest scheme offers a total of 7,500 houses in Loknayakpuram, Siraspur, and Narela across the EWS, LIG, MIG, and HIG category of flats. The bookings will open May 27.

news.title: Shikhar Dhawan buys flat in DLF's The Dahlias for ₹69 crore
news.para: Dhawan has bought a 6,040 square feet apartment in the DLF's latest super-luxury project 'The Dahlias' on Golf Course Raod, Gurugram, the research firm said.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves state housing policy 2025
news.para: As part of the implementation strategy, the cabinet has cleared the formation of a ₹20,000 crore 'Maha Aawas Nidhi' at the state level to finance large-scale housing projects under the new policy framework.

news.title: DLF sets sales bookings target at ₹20-22,000 crore for FY26: Managing director
news.para: ​On Monday, the DLF reported record sales bookings of Rs 21,223 crore in 2024-25, an increase of 44 per cent from Rs 14,778 crore in the preceding financial year.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty gets Sebi nod for ₹792 crore IPO
news.para: Amitabh Bachchan, Shah Rukh Khan, Ajay Devgn, Hrithik Roshan, Sara Ali Khan, Ektaa Kapoor, Tiger Shroff, and Rajkumar Rao, all have recently bought small stakes in Sri Lotus Developers.

news.title: Abu Dhabi's Lunate, Brookfield start $1 billion residential property venture
news.para: The venture will focus on "developing high-quality build-to-sell and opportunistic buy-to-sell residential assets" across the UAE, Saudi Arabia, and other markets in the Middle East, the statement said.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises ₹2,000 crore debt at 7.21%
news.para: Ritwik Bhattacharjee, chief executive officer, Embassy REIT said, ""We maintain a well-diversified and conservative debt book, and this refinancing positions us well to capitalize on future growth opportunities."

news.title: Cement sector outlook brightens as demand, prices improve: Nuvama Research
news.para: It said, "We believe the outlook for the cement space is improving as both volumes and prices are likely to log an uptick going ahead, aided by a low base of FY25E".

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Conditional waivers granted for residential construction under overhead power lines
news.para: The exemptions were granted by exercising rules 62 and 63 of the Central Electricity Authority (Measures Relating to Safety and Electrical Supply) Regulations 2023 based on the recommendations of a three-member committee set up by state govt.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body releases list of 176 dangerous buildings ahead of monsoon
news.para: The list of buildings has been put up on the KDMC website. The civic body has appealed to occupants of these buildings to vacate them and move to safer places ahead of the monsoon.
